oking at the filtering block around lines 591-598, if Fix 2 fires and nulls out the structural heading, these lines will correctly skip the filtering since the translation-as-structural-heading shouldn't be used to remove valid candidates.\n\nFor the implementation, I'm going to use a separate `activeStructuralHeading` variable to track the post-fix structural heading, which keeps things cleaner than trying to reassign `firstStructuralHeading` with type annotations. Now I need to implement the actual changes: adding the `stripDiacritics` function, updating `SECTION_LABELS` and `isSectionLabel` to handle diacritics properly. Fixing the type annotation...\n\nI'm realizing the simplest approach is to type `firstStructuralHeading` as nullable and assign it conditionally based on whether we find a matching heading in `rawScored`, using the find method to locate the element by text content. I see the issue now—`baseHeading` is either a structured element or `undefined`, so when I use the `&&` operator, it returns `undefined` if falsy, or the result of the expression. That means `firstStructuralHeading` should be typed as `undefined` or the full heading object type. For the fix, I just need to use `undefined` instead of `null` to match the actual behavior.\n\nSince `newHeading` is already an element from `rawScored` (pulled from `structuralCandidates`), I can simplify the reassignment—I don't need to search for it again, I can just assign it directly with a fallback to `undefined`.\n\nNow I'm ready to make the actual edits. First, I need to add the `stripDiacritics` function before `isSectionLabel` and update `SECTION_LABELS` to include diacritic-stripped versions of Polish words...\n\nAdding the diacritics utility and expanding section labels... Verifying the diacritic stripping is working correctly across the Polish terms...\n\nNow I need to make those fixes: hoist the translation candidates variable to the outer scope, update the bilingual filter logic, add the structural bonus reassignment after detecting bilingual content, and switch that first structural heading variable to use `let` instead of `const`.\n\nFor hoisting `translationCandidates`, I need to move it before the `prePos0` check, but since `nearbyAllCaps` is defined inside that block, I'll need to type it based on the structure of the `scored` array instead.\n\nWriting the updated code... I'm working through the variable declaration order—`scored` is already defined before I need `translationCandidates`, so I can hoist it out of the conditional block and declare it right after `scored` to keep the scope cleaner.\n\nNow I need to check where `structuralCandidates` comes from and verify the type inference for `firstStructuralHeading` when I change it from `const` to `let`. The `scored` array itself is const, but since it contains mutable objects, I can modify their properties like `score` without TypeScript complaining—the type doesn't have `readonly` modifiers, so mutation is allowed.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the actual edits I need to make: stripping diacritics from the section labels and updating the comparison logic, changing `firstStructuralHeading` to `let` so it can be reassigned, hoisting the `translationCandidates` declaration before the threshold scoring block, and removing the duplicate declaration inside the conditional.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6539,"cache_read_input_tokens":38094,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6539},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69be8f57-504b-40bc-8d20-876849e39e96","uuid":"0acd9453-7a81-44bb-be99-48106cee5505"}
