{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YYez8Z6nhMNwroRSh9PDjD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three fixes are implemented and all 33 tests pass:\n\n1. **Fix 1** (bilingual join contamination): Extended the translation filter to suppress multi-line joins that embed the translation as a suffix (`endsWith`) or substring (`includes(\" \" + tLower)`), not just as a prefix.\n\n2. **Fix 2** (structural bonus misallocation): After bilingual detection, if `firstStructuralHeading` is identified as a translation, the structural bonus (+0.10) is patched out of the `scored` array and `firstStructuralHeading` is updated to the next best non-translation structural candidate.\n\n3. **Fix 3** (diacritic-stripped section labels): Added `stripDiacritics()` using NFKD normalization, stored Polish section labels without diacritics, and updated `isSectionLabel` to strip diacritics before lookup — so `\"SKLADNIKI\"` (OCR-corrupted) now correctly matches `\"składniki\"`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":681,"cache_read_input_tokens":56002,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":681},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69be8f57-504b-40bc-8d20-876849e39e96","uuid":"055e5778-1049-4967-af90-4fba9cbb6995"}
