{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HJZucNPiLokvTpwkkPepcY","type":"tool_result","content":"   490→  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   491→  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   492→    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n   493→    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   494→    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n   495→      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n   496→      : 1.0;\n   497→\n   498→    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n   499→    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   500→      ? 0.08\n   501→      : 0;\n   502→\n   503→    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   504→    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   505→\n   506→    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   507→    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   508→    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   509→    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n   510→    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   511→    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   512→    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   513→  });\n   514→\n   515→  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   516→    return undefined;\n   517→  }\n   518→\n   519→  // --- Pre-threshold bilingual title detection ---\n   520→  // When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 is followed by an ALL_CAPS candidate\n   521→  // at position ≤ 2 that is semantically similar to it, this is a bilingual recipe\n   522→  // page (e.g., Polish title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization). Suppress confirmed\n   523→  // translation candidates before computing threshold so their bonuses don't inflate\n   524→  // the threshold beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n   525→  // Note: we check position ≤ 2 (local proximity), not global ALL_CAPS count, so\n   526→  // section headers later in the document (SKŁADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc.) are irrelevant.\n   527→  let translationCandidates: typeof scored = [];\n   528→  let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n   529→  const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n   530→  if (prePos0) {\n   531→    const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n   532→      (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 && s.origin === \"single\"\n   533→    );\n   534→    const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016VPztTugtQjHecoZo6zBy1","session_id":"69be8f57-504b-40bc-8d20-876849e39e96","uuid":"bbb387be-4969-440e-8006-9ce959e1b99a"}
